      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my wifi router has a solid red light on the \"internet\" icon. i tried turning it off and on but nothing changed. what should i do?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A solid red light on your router's internet icon is a classic sign of a \"stuck\" or \"hung\" connection, which is a very common issue for those who have been dealing with the internet for too long. It's like when a friend is trying to talk to you but the signal is so weak that they can barely hear you, resulting in a static-filled voice that sounds like a broken radio.\n\nSince turning it off and on didn't fix it, the router is likely stuck in a loop waiting for a signal that never comes back. You might need to try a \"hard reset\" by unplugging the power cord from the wall outlet and leaving it there for about 30 seconds before plugging it back in. This is like giving the router a little nudge to wake it up from its sleep mode, which is often what it's doing right now.\n\nIf that doesn't work, try restarting your modem or router by unplugging both devices from the wall, waiting 60 seconds, and then plugging them back in. Sometimes, the modem needs a bit of time to \"reboot\" its internal clock and clear any accumulated data that has built up.\n\nIf you've tried these steps and the",
